For the last few years most cannabis industry observers have downplayed the more difficult operating environment that lied ahead, have had unrealistic short and intermediate term industry forecasts, missed the impact of inflation on spending, miscalculated the softness in

wholesale markets and the slow state rollouts, overstated the prospects for legislation, paid too high valuations (4-7x sales). Though bulls have been steadfastly confident they have ignored all these factors and the consistent company downgrades in outlook and $MSOS has

dropped from $60 to $11. The good news is that now expectations are more realistic, enterprise values now only 0.5-2x sales and management teams have grown more professional and have been beefed up. Importantly we seem to be at a legislative inflection point.
